text: Jamshid Khilolovich Karimov (Tajik: Ҷамшед Хилолович Каримов, ; born August 4, 1940) is a Tajikistani politician. He was the Prime Minister of Tajikistan between December 2, 1994 and February 8, 1996. He is a cousin of former President of Uzbekistan, Islam Karimov. From June 20, 1997 to 2002 he was Tajik Ambassador to China. He was born in Dushanbe. ==References== Category:1940 births Category:Living people Category:Prime ministers of Tajikistan
